# =============================================================================
# lnd — the Lightning Network Daemon, the reference implementation of a full
#       Lightning Network node in Go.  Lightning Labs's production Bitcoin
#       Lightning Network node software, used to send / receive instant low-
#       fee payments over the Bitcoin Lightning Network.  Speaks the BOLT
#       specs (Basis of Lightning Technology), maintains channels to peers,
#       performs HTLC routing, watchtower interaction, on-chain wallet
#       management, autopilot channel selection, hash time-locked-contract
#       enforcement, gossip propagation, and a gRPC + REST control API
#       (consumed by lncli, BOS, Thunderhub, RTL, Zeus, etc).  Runs against
#       bitcoind / btcd / neutrino backends; ships with Tor (v2/v3),
#       Let's Encrypt, watchtower client/server, autopilot, channel-backup,
#       MPP/AMP payments, channel-acceptor RPC, key locker macaroons, and
#       a clustered HA mode via etcd/postgres.
